      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt and mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 160°C fan. Butter and line the rectangular tin. Melt the {{unsalted-butter}}, {{black-treacle}}, {{golden-syrup}}, and {{dark-brown-sugar}} together in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves. Do not let the mixture boil. Remove from the heat and stir in the {{whole-milk}}, then the beaten {{eggs}}. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "treacle batter",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yiqhv000048v4fma7cbqe"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": it will be dark, liquid, and strongly scented.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fold in the dry ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In a large bowl, combine the {{plain-flour}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Pour the warm treacle mixture into the dry ingredients and stir until smooth. The batter will be thin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 38 to 42 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the batter into the prepared tin. Bake for 38 to 42 minutes until the top feels firm when pressed lightly and a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. The cake will sink slightly in the centre as it cools, this is normal. Cool completely in the tin before cutting. The cake will be stickier and more flavourful the following day.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
